                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.794,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 152701,
                                "text": "We have opinions this morning beginning with Justice Kagan in Number 10-1542, Holder versus Gutierrez and 10-1543, Holder versus Sawyers."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.794,
                        "stop": 296.882,
                        "byte_start": 152701,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.794,
                                "stop": 24.684,
                                "byte_start": 152701,
                                "byte_stop": 204215,
                                "text": "These cases concern the reasonableness of the Board of Immigration Appeals or BIA\u0027s interpretation of a federal immigration statute, which I\u0027ll refer to as Section 1229 (b) (a)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.684,
                                "stop": 40.99,
                                "byte_start": 204215,
                                "byte_stop": 269521,
                                "text": "That statute gives the Attorney General discretion to allow otherwise removable aliens, usually aliens who have committed a crime, to stay in the country so long as they satisfy certain criteria, two of which are relevant here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.99,
                                "stop": 56.064,
                                "byte_start": 269521,
                                "byte_stop": 329812,
                                "text": "First, subsection (a) (1) of the statute requires the alien to have held the status of a lawful permanent resident, in immigration lingo that\u0027s called LPR status, for at least five years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.064,
                                "stop": 69.873,
                                "byte_start": 329812,
                                "byte_stop": 384982,
                                "text": "Second, subsection (a) (2) requires the alien to have continuously resided in the United States for at least seven years after being lawfully admitted, whatever his immigration status is."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.873,
                                "stop": 76.286,
                                "byte_start": 384982,
                                "byte_stop": 410687,
                                "text": "Now, there\u0027s a question about applying this statute to aliens who have lived in the country as children."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.286,
                                "stop": 84.666,
                                "byte_start": 410687,
                                "byte_stop": 444228,
                                "text": "Sometimes a child will enter the country lawfully or obtain LPR status after one of his parents does."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.666,
                                "stop": 93.926,
                                "byte_start": 444228,
                                "byte_stop": 481217,
                                "text": "In those situations, a parent might qualify for relief under the statute while his child, considered independently, does not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.926,
                                "stop": 111.338,
                                "byte_start": 481217,
                                "byte_stop": 550912,
                                "text": "So the question arises, should the BIA require each alien to meet 1229 (b) (a)\u0027s requirements on his own or should it impute a parent\u0027s years of LPR status or residence to his child."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.338,
                                "stop": 115.045,
                                "byte_start": 550912,
                                "byte_stop": 565750,
                                "text": "The cases before us illustrate how the issue comes up."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.045,
                                "stop": 119.954,
                                "byte_start": 565750,
                                "byte_stop": 585289,
                                "text": "There are two of them, but I will give you the facts of just one as an example."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.954,
                                "stop": 128.626,
                                "byte_start": 585289,
                                "byte_stop": 619980,
                                "text": "Carlos Martinez Gutierrez entered the country illegally with his family in 1989 when he was five years old."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.626,
                                "stop": 133.626,
                                "byte_start": 619980,
                                "byte_stop": 640042,
                                "text": "His father was lawfully admitted as an LPR just two years later."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.626,
                                "stop": 159.034,
                                "byte_start": 640042,
                                "byte_stop": 741710,
                                "text": "But Martinez Gutierrez was neither lawfully admitted nor given LPR status until 2003, so when Martinez Gutierrez committed a crime two years later in 2005, and that -- and that crime rendered him removable, he couldn\u0027t satisfy either subsection of 1229 (b) (a) without help from his father."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.034,
                                "stop": 163.969,
                                "byte_start": 741710,
                                "byte_stop": 761354,
                                "text": "The BIA has held that aliens, like Martinez Gutierrez, are out of luck."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.969,
                                "stop": 169.349,
                                "byte_start": 761354,
                                "byte_stop": 782879,
                                "text": "It is required each alien to independently satisfy 1229 (b) (a)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.349,
                                "stop": 192.293,
                                "byte_start": 782879,
                                "byte_stop": 874726,
                                "text": "Children don\u0027t get to borrow years of residence or immigration status from their parents, but the Ninth Circuit concluded that this position was unreasonable and held that the Board must impute a parent\u0027s immigration history to his or her child for any years in which the child lived with the parent as an unemancipated minor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.293,
                                "stop": 204.82,
                                "byte_start": 874726,
                                "byte_stop": 924776,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to decide this question to determine whether the BIA\u0027s no imputation policy is based on a reasonable construction of 1229 (b) (a)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 204.82,
                                "stop": 224.587,
                                "byte_start": 924776,
                                "byte_stop": 1003875,
                                "text": "The construction need only be reasonable, it need not be the only construction or even the best one because we give deference to agencies when they interpret the statutes they administer and today, we hold that the BIA\u0027s interpretation of 1229 (b) (a) is reasonable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.587,
                                "stop": 232.571,
                                "byte_start": 1003875,
                                "byte_stop": 1035849,
                                "text": "The Board\u0027s position is consistent with the statutory language which doesn\u0027t mention much less require imputation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.571,
                                "stop": 239.345,
                                "byte_start": 1035849,
                                "byte_stop": 1062912,
                                "text": "Instead, the statute simply calls for the alien to meet the prerequisites for relief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.345,
                                "stop": 254.879,
                                "byte_start": 1062912,
                                "byte_stop": 1125083,
                                "text": "Gutierrez contends that this language doesn\u0027t foreclose imputation, but even if that\u0027s true, that is not enough to require the Board to adopt the policy and that so of a number of Martinez Gutierrez\u0027s arguments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 254.879,
                                "stop": 265.64,
                                "byte_start": 1125083,
                                "byte_stop": 1168133,
                                "text": "He has presented a variety of reasons why the Board might read the statutes to permit imputation, but none requiring the Board to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.64,
                                "stop": 280.593,
                                "byte_start": 1168133,
                                "byte_stop": 1227901,
                                "text": "We also reject Gutierrez\u0027s argument that the BIA\u0027s policy should be struck down because it is inconsistent with the Board\u0027s decision to allow imputation between parents and children in other immigration contexts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 280.593,
                                "stop": 289.997,
                                "byte_start": 1227901,
                                "byte_stop": 1265518,
                                "text": "We think the BIA has done an adequate job of explaining why imputation might make sense in some areas but not in others."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 289.997,
                                "stop": 294.606,
                                "byte_start": 1265518,
                                "byte_stop": 1283908,
                                "text": "We, therefore, reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 294.606,
                                "stop": 296.882,
                                "byte_start": 1283908,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
